The paper deals with the study of phase transition phenomenon of NP complete problems, specifically the problem of counting solutions of Constraint Satisfaction Problems (#CSP). This makes it likely to belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The use of random models and experimental results suggest a connection to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the proposed approximate algorithm indicates a possible connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
